head pressure is there a doc out there i'm writing this for a friend as i'm concerned for about a month and a half he says his head hurts he described it as pressure in the back of his head he said sometimes it's hard to drive because it hurts so much he said that he gets odd thoughts very tired and has been getting angry for no reason any clues as to if this can be major i told him to call a doc but he is just scared that something big is wrong that they'll have to drill in his skull any advice would be great thanks he needs to make an appointment with a neurologist and get an mri done to rule out any type of tumor i have a condition called intracranial hypertension aka psuedotumor cerebri the symptoms of this disease mimick that of a brain tumor but is actually increased cf fluid around the brain and spine causing pressure on the optic nerves it can make you go blind as well as intense headaches and visual disturbances i received a brain shunt to help keep the fluid level stable by draining some of it into my peronial cavity let him know that i have had a drill in my skull and its not bad at all i made it its been a little over years now and i have my life back tell him not to mess around i understand he is scared but if its something major he needs to start fixing it before its too late i would rather have another drill in my skull than dieing Benign intracranial hypertension Brain tumor Traumatic brain injury Intracranial pressure Cephalic disorder Syringomyelia Hydrocephalus Stroke Brain Lumbar puncture Migraine Multiple sclerosis Chronic fatigue syndrome History of brain imaging Concussion of the brain Glaucoma Subdural hematoma Hypertension Aortic dissection Head injury Acromegaly Hemorrhagic stroke Neurology Subarachnoid hemorrhage Human brain Prostate cancer Epilepsy Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Growth hormone treatment Apoplexy Spina bifida Eye Brain abscess Aspartame Neurofibromatosis type I Meningitis Decompression sickne